00266 /// @name Encoding
00267 //@{
00268 ///   This is the main interface to the encoder. The array should be
00269 ///   at most 15 bytes long. The ilen parameter should indiciate
00270 ///   this length. If the array is too short, the encoder may fail to
00271 ///   encode the request.  Failure is indicated by a return value of
00272 ///   type #xed_error_enum_t that is not equal to
00273 ///   #XED_ERROR_NONE. Otherwise, #XED_ERROR_NONE is returned and the
00274 ///   length of the encoded instruction is returned in olen.
00275 ///
00276 /// @param r encoder request description (#xed_encoder_request_t), includes mode info
00277 /// @param array the encoded instruction bytes are stored here
00278 /// @param ilen the input length of array.
00279 /// @param olen the actual  length of array used for encoding
00280 /// @return success/failure as a #xed_error_enum_t
00281 /// @ingroup ENC
00282 XED_DLL_EXPORT xed_error_enum_t
00283 xed_encode(xed_encoder_request_t* r,
00284            xed_uint8_t* array, 
00285            const unsigned int ilen,
00286            unsigned int* olen);
00287 
00288 /// This function will attempt to encode a NOP of exactly ilen
00289 /// bytes. If such a NOP is not encodeable, then false will be returned.
00290 ///
00291 /// @param array the encoded instruction bytes are stored here
00292 /// @param  ilen the input length array.
00293 /// @return success/failure as a #xed_error_enum_t
00294 /// @ingroup ENC
00295 XED_DLL_EXPORT xed_error_enum_t
00296 xed_encode_nop(xed_uint8_t* array, 
00297                const unsigned int ilen);
00298 //@}
